<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-06T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-06T18:00:00-05:00" n="570" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d570">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5231/968: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-06T19:00:00-04:00">May 6, 1935—7
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>24. Your No. 27, May 6, 1 p.m., last paragraph. First meeting with
                                Spanish negotiators took place May 3. Negotiations still in
                                preliminary stage but we are meeting daily in order to expedite
                                matters as much as possible. We shall keep you advised of any
                                developments of moment.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>